value.0: Hullo, <mister/missus>. Ya seem a bitta lost. New in town?

Good <man/woman>! Lemme see 'em!

Well... which one you wanna hear, <mister/missus>?

"Jarlabanki had this stone put up in his own lifetime. 
And he made this causeway for his soul's sake."

If a fella here poops in some God's pool, he mus' make a sacerfice... to keep his soul frem bein' squashed later on, ya know. Well, vain bugger's put up a stone fer the Gods, and never fail to mention their own names onnit... haha. Daft sods!

"Hjallmar had this stone put up in his own honor. 
He took Cnut's protection money. 
May the Gods help his soul."

Hehe.. dis one's funny... you see... sum fam'lies 'ere, they are pirates, ya know. They call 'emselves brave warriors, but they are raiders an' scum non'theless.  Some fam'lies are clever, though, an' they let other people pay 'em not to trash 'em up! Pretection money! 

Well, other fam'lies are even more clever, an' they simply steal the pretection money! They jus' sit here, and mug the scum that comes back, an' take their money! Smart, ent it? 'elps Them looks like Cave Bears an' all, o' course.

"Eskill Skulkason had this stone raised to himself. 
Ever will stand this memorial which Eskill made!"

We ent proud at all 'ere, ent we?! See... the peeps here think they are closer to them Gods than their own mother!

"Vigmund had this stone carved in memory of himself, the cleverest of men."

See? They think they are damn clever in 'ere. Hehe. Well, clever... my donkey's quite clever too, if ya git me gist.
Yes, 'course! I ent one of those *cough* simple folk o'er there, ya know.
Urrrr....

<StartHighlight>Bows over to you and whispers</Start> 

<StartAction>Hush! It's me, Chevallier LeClerk! I keep an eye on Amia's interest here!</Start>

Them peeps hunt animal fer are pelts and skins. Main 'traction, howevah, be the fact that it's so bloody cold 'ere. Many of them merchant houses frem abroad have a storage 'ere to keep their stuff in prime condition, <mister/missus>. 
The 'eadquarters of the Amian Traders Federation are located on that small island on the other side of the bay, fer instance. The money frem them merchants kinda trickles down the local 'conomy, ya know.
Umm.. because they dun know ya. An' if they dun know ya, ya mus' be bad, so they ent gunna know ya. Logic? Yus!

*bows over to you and whispers*

<StartAction>Them are re-tar-ded. Comes frem the bloody cold, I guesses. Mebbe frem inbreedin', though. Who knows, who cares?!</Start>
Well, <lad/lass>, ya dunt have to look inna lie- ..umm law-.. nopes... damn... summing with lies, an' it's git books...

Yus! Them gits 'ere ent got one. Much too civ'lised fer 'em.
Anyways, ya dunt need one 'ere... them buggers chissel god knows what on silly stones in the countryside, ya know.
Lemme 'elp you. 'ere's a notebook an' a pencil. You look 'round, draw them runes on the paper an' come back when you gots 4 of 'em. I will tell you what's onnit. Mos' of 'em are a good laugh.

<StartHighlight>*looks at your face and squints his eyes*</Start>
You?! Nopes! Nevah seen that mug b'fore!

<StartAction>*looks decidedly uninterested*</Start>
O! Int'resting.
If it ent me pal <FirstName>! How are ya?!
Kinda looser's town 'ere, ent it, m'<lord/lady>?
Nopes.
I have noted down the 4 runestone inscriptions, Sir.
I heard enough, Sir.
The one I found on Mt Firth
Interesting!
The one I found in the Gray Forest
Interesting!
The one I found in Niflwood
Interesting!
The one I found in Kjalarnes
Interesting!
Can I ask you some questions?
Where did you learn this silly accent of yours? That just can't be natural, you know.
Hmm?
Rrrright you are...
How do the folks here survive?
I see...
Why are the people so unfriendly to me?
Umm... not really...
Well, as a matter of fact, I do care. Is there any place where I can find some ... books on history or something on this island?
Library?
No way! Much too cold outside!
OK! Will do!
Hey! Don't you recognise me?
Haha, I was just kidding you. I am <FirstName>, fresh from Amia.
Yes, sir, I am.
